# Custom Fonts Directory

Place your custom font files here.

## Supported Formats
- .woff2 (recommended - best compression)
- .woff (fallback for older browsers)
- .ttf / .otf (not recommended for web, use woff2 instead)

## Example Structure
```
public/fonts/
├── MyCustomFont-Regular.woff2
├── MyCustomFont-Bold.woff2
├── MyCustomFont-Italic.woff2
└── MyCustomFont-BoldItalic.woff2
```

## Usage
After adding fonts here, import them in src/app/layout.tsx using Next.js localFont:

```tsx
import localFont from 'next/font/local';

const myFont = localFont({
  src: [
    {
      path: '../public/fonts/MyCustomFont-Regular.woff2',
      weight: '400',
      style: 'normal',
    },
    {
      path: '../public/fonts/MyCustomFont-Bold.woff2',
      weight: '700',
      style: 'normal',
    },
  ],
  variable: '--font-my-custom',
});
```

Then add the variable to your body className in layout.tsx.
